  "text": "With regard to incident IHD, our data are consistent with the hypothesis that high dietary atherogenicity or thrombogenicity scores are associated with increased risk of subsequent IHD. The magnitude of the differences is similar to those for saturates or polyunsaturates, expressed as a percentage of total fatty acids ; slightly greater than those for saturates and polyunsaturates, expressed as a percentage of total energy; and greater than that for animal fdt, expressed as a percentage of total energy ( 9 O h of the population SD; [CITATION_1] .",
